cs.AR, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper deals with automated toolflow for optimizing the performance of CNN models on FPGA devices. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AR (Hardware Architecture for Robotics and Automation). However, since the paper focuses on computer vision tasks, it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). Additionally, the paper involves machine learning techniques, which could place it in cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, since the paper deals with hardware implementation, it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
